  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors assessed with documented requiredLevel and achievedLevel; seven factors exhibit achieved levels marginally below required levels, and six factors are scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision: Not accepted — the structured evidence demonstrates that the model does not meet the minimum credibility thresholds required for a Class III device at MRL 5.",
